{% # Core Assets v1.4.0 %}

{% comment %}
  Changelog
  - v1.4.0 — drop the `.shopify-section--exploration` stylesheet block. Bleed-API decisions landed with the subgrid migration; the 10 `exploration--bleed--*` scaffolds + hub + experimental `exploration-*` blocks + supporting snippets were deleted alongside this edit. `exploration--subgrid.liquid` carries its own self-contained chrome styles.
  - v1.3.0 — drop `display: block` from the `.shopify-section--exploration token-section` exploration-scaffold override. Override defeated the substrate's bleed grid post-subgrid-migration, leaving bleed modifiers on experimental blocks (now stripped of internal bleed CSS) with nothing to gate — bleed cases rendered as plain block flow on individual `exploration--bleed--*` pages. Keep `padding-block` (block-direction; doesn't conflict with grid).
  - v1.2.0 — split `core.css` into four per-layer files (`layer-base.css`, `layer-reset.css`, `layer-theme.css`, `layer-utilities.css`) to circumvent Shopify's 15360-byte `inline_asset_content` cap. Each layer is captured via `utility--inline-asset` and concatenated, then routed through `utility--asset-loader` (mirrors the dynamic-styles pattern). No load-mechanism change — still one inline `<style>` block on first paint.
  - v1.1.0 — drop `lab.css` template-suffix branch (lab concept not in this theme)
  - v1.0.0 — initial
{% endcomment %}

{% doc %}
  @description
  Emits the theme's head assets in order:
  1. Core layers inline (`layer-base` → `layer-reset` → `layer-theme` → `layer-utilities`, concatenated and minified into one `<style>` block) + `core.js` preloaded as an ES module
  2. Dynamic styles (from `utility--font-face` + `utility--css-variables`) inlined as a second minified block
  3. ES module import map

  Intended to be called once in `layout/theme.liquid` inside <head>. See `.context/docs/asset-loading.md` for the strategy catalog used at each step.

  @example {% render 'utility--core-assets' %}
{% enddoc %}

{% liquid
  # Primary: per-layer core CSS inline + core.js preload
  capture core_layers
    render 'utility--inline-asset', asset_name: 'layer-base.css'
    render 'utility--inline-asset', asset_name: 'layer-reset.css'
    render 'utility--inline-asset', asset_name: 'layer-theme.css'
    render 'utility--inline-asset', asset_name: 'layer-utilities.css'
  endcapture
  render 'utility--asset-loader', css: 'inline', css_content: core_layers, js: false
  render 'utility--asset-loader', name: 'core', css: false, js: 'preload'

  # Secondary: dynamic styles (fonts + CSS variables)
  capture dynamic_style
    render 'utility--font-face'
    render 'utility--css-variables'
  endcapture
  render 'utility--asset-loader', css: 'inline', css_content: dynamic_style, js: false

  # Tertiary: ES module import map
  render 'utility--import-map'
%}

